{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Björn Daelemans | fullname = Björn Daelemans | image = | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1977|12|11|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Ekeren]], [[Belgium]] | death_date = | death_place = | height = {{height|m=1.79}} | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | currentclub = | years1 = 1995–1996 | clubs1 = [[Beerschot AC|Germinal Ekeren]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | years2 = 1996–1997 | clubs2 = [[R. Cappellen F.C.|Cappellen]] | caps2 = | goals2 = | years3 = 1997–2001 | clubs3 = [[K.F.C. Verbroedering Geel|Verbroedering Geel]] | caps3 = 117 | goals3 = 38 | years4 = 2001–2006 | clubs4 = [[RBC Roosendaal]] | caps4 = 123 | goals4 = 12 | years5 = 2005 | clubs5 = → [[K.F.C. Verbroedering Geel|Verbroedering Geel]] (loan) | caps5 = 13 | goals5 = 7 | years6 = 2006–2008 | clubs6 = [[Heracles Almelo]] | caps6 = 20 | goals6 = 0 | years7 = 2008–2010 | clubs7 = [[AS Verbroedering Geel|Verbroedering Geel-Meerhout]] | caps7 = | goals7 = }}
'''Björn Daelemans''' (born 11 December 1977) is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] former [[Association football|footballer]]. He predominantly played as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]], but later in his career he also appeared as [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right back]].
Daelemans was born in [[Ekeren]]<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/bjoern-daelemans/|title=Björn Daelemans|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Worldfootball.net|access-date=16 July 2016}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ronaldzwiers.0catch.com/Spelers/D/Daelemans,%20Bjorn/Bjorn%20Daelemans.htm|title=Björn Daelemans|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Ronald's Voetbalstatistieken|language=Dutch|access-date=16 July 2016}}</ref> and made his debut in professional football in the 1995–96 season when playing for [[Beerschot AC|Germinal Ekeren]] in the [[Belgian First Division A]].<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":2">{{Cite web|url=http://www.footballdatabase.eu/football.joueurs.bjorn.daelemans.22330.en.html|title=Football : Bjorn Daelemans|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=FootballDatabase.eu|access-date=16 July 2016}}</ref> The next season, he played for [[R. Cappellen F.C.|Cappellen F.C.]] in the [[Belgian Second Division]].<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":2" />
He then moved to [[K.F.C. Verbroedering Geel|Verbroedering Geel]] from the same level, where he would play between 1997 and 2001.<ref name=":0" /> In the 1998–99 season, he helped them achieve promotion to the First Division A [[Belgian Second Division play-offs|through play-offs]], contributing 17 goals from 33 league appearances.<ref name=":1" /> After being relegated at the end of the following season, Daelemans played one more season for the club in the Second Division.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":2" />
In the summer of 2001, he moved to the [[Netherlands]], signing with [[Eerste Divisie]] club [[RBC Roosendaal]].<ref name=":0" /> In his first season, he made 28 appearances (four goals) and saw the club promoted to the [[Eredivisie]] through [[2001–02 Eerste Divisie|play-offs]].<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /> During his time with RBC, Daelemans appeared frequently, both as a starter and from the bench,<ref name=":0" /> except between January 2005 and June 2005, when he was loaned out to his old club Verbroedering Geel.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vi.nl/nieuws/daelemans-terug-naar-verbroedering-geel.htm|title=Daelemans terug naar Verbroedering Geel|last=|first=|date=18 January 2005|website=|publisher=VI.nl|language=Dutch|access-date=16 July 2016}}</ref> At the end of the 2005–06 season, RBC were relegated from the Eredivisie and Daelemans was released from the club.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vi.nl/nieuws/wegen-van-rbc-en-daelemans-scheiden.htm|title=Wegen van RBC en Daelemans scheiden|last=|first=|date=1 April 2006|website=|publisher=VI.nl|language=Dutch|access-date=16 July 2016}}</ref>
In May 2006, he signed for [[Heracles Almelo]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vi.nl/nieuws/daelemans-verruilt-rbc-voor-heracles-almelo.htm|title=Daelemans verruilt RBC voor Heracles Almelo|last=|first=|date=1 May 2006|website=|publisher=VI.nl|language=Dutch|access-date=16 July 2016}}</ref> where he was asked to play as [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right back]] rather than as a forward.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tubantia.nl/sport/heracles/wennen-aan-nieuwe-club-en-positie-1.2419623|title=Wennen aan nieuwe club en positie|last=|first=|date=26 July 2006|website=|publisher=Tubantia|language=Dutch|access-date=16 July 2016}}</ref> After two seasons, in which he made 20 Eredivisie appearances, he was released.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vi.nl/nieuws/heracles-neemt-afscheid-van-michalke-en-daelemans.htm|title=Heracles neemt afscheid van Michalke en Daelemans|last=|first=|date=18 May 2008|website=|publisher=VI.nl|language=Dutch|access-date=16 July 2016}}</ref>
He ended his career with [[AS Verbroedering Geel|Verbroedering Geel-Meerhout]] in the [[Belgian Fourth Division]], playing for them between 2008 and 2010.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2" />
