'''Laurie Stephens''' (born March 5, 1984) is an alpine [[Monoskiing|monoskier]] who has [[spina bifida]]. She has won multiple medals for the [[United States at the Paralympics]].<ref>[http://ipc.infostradasports.com/asp/lib/TheASP.asp?pageid=8937&sportid=564&personid=910566 IPC bio]</ref> She has also had success at the [[IPC Alpine Skiing World Cup]]. Outside of sports she studied therapeutic recreation at the [[University of New Hampshire]].<ref>[http://www.fosters.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20100312/GJSPORTS_01/703129857/-1/FOSNEWS Article in Foster's Daily Democrat from March 12, 2010]</ref>

